        <h1>LeetCode 961: N-Repeated Element in Size 2N Array (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an integer array nums with the following properties: nums.length == 2 * n. nums contains n
                + 1
                unique elements. Exactly one element of nums is repeated n times. Return the element that is repeated n
                times.
                The key insight is that since one element appears n times in an array of size 2n, with only n+1 unique
                elements total, the repeated element must appear within any window of 3 consecutive elements (pigeonhole
                principle). We can check adjacent pairs, and if none match, check edge cases where the repeated element
                wraps around the array boundaries.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,3,3] → Output: 3. The element 3 is repeated n=2 times.
                Input: nums = [2,1,2,5,3,2] → Output: 2. The element 2 is repeated n=3 times.
                Input: nums = [5,1,5,2,5,3,5,4] → Output: 5. The element 5 is repeated n=4 times.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int repeatedNTimes(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        // Check adjacent elements
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n - 1; i++) {
            if (arr[i] == arr[i + 1])
                return arr[i];
        }
        // Handle edge overlap cases
        if (arr[0] == arr[n - 1] || arr[0] == arr[n - 2]) return arr[0];
        if (arr[1] == arr[n - 1]) return arr[1];
        return -1;
    }
};</code></pre>
